# Why This Works

The vulnerable application renders user-controlled input directly inside a Django template.

Although Django templates prevent arbitrary Python execution, they still expose internal objects through the rendering context.

The `{% debug %}` tag reveals every available variable, including the global `settings` object.

Since Django templates allow attribute access, the attacker can simply evaluate:

```django
{{settings.SECRET_KEY}}
```

to disclose one of the application's most sensitive configuration values.

---

# Impact

Disclosure of Django's `SECRET_KEY` can compromise multiple security mechanisms, including:

- Forging signed session cookies
- Forging password reset tokens
- Forging CSRF tokens
- Forging signed URLs
- Manipulating cryptographically signed application data
- Facilitating privilege escalation depending on application design

Although this lab only demonstrates information disclosure, exposure of the secret key could ultimately lead to complete application compromise.

