---

# Root Cause

The application allows user-controlled template code to be rendered by the Django template engine.

Additionally, sensitive objects such as `settings` are exposed to the template context, allowing attackers to access confidential configuration values.

---

# Remediation

- Never render user-controlled template code.
- Avoid exposing template editors to untrusted users.
- Enable strict template sandboxing where available.
- Remove unnecessary objects from the template context.
- Disable debugging functionality in production.
- Prevent sensitive configuration objects from being accessible within templates.

