# Conclusion

This lab demonstrates that Server-Side Template Injection does not always require Remote Code Execution to be dangerous. Even within the relatively restricted Django template engine, attackers can leverage built-in functionality to enumerate internal objects and disclose highly sensitive configuration data such as the application's `SECRET_KEY`.

Compromise of this key can undermine multiple authentication and integrity mechanisms, potentially enabling attackers to forge signed data, hijack user sessions, or escalate their privileges within the application.
